      "message": "Yeah, that reads somewhat consistently with what I\u0027m seeing in profiles.\n\nI don\u0027t think we need to go down the path here in this CL... it\u0027s not the slow part as far as I can tell.\n\nThe other part mixed in here switching from std::vector\u003cuint8_t\u003e to SkTDArray\u003cuint8_t\u003e is probably still worth looking at.  We are seeing a silly amount of time being spent zeroing the new bytes when calling std::vector::resize(), one at a time!  Dropping in SkTDArray\u003cuint8_t\u003e was an easy way to demonstrate that, but I think it can also be done with a custom allocator that defines construct() as a noop.",
